==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxychloric
<hw>Ox`y*chlo"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Oxy-</ets>
<sd>(a)</sd> + <ets>chloric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating in general, certain
compounds containing oxygen and chlorine.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Formerly designating an acid now called <altname>perchloric
acid</altname>. See <er>Perchloric</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxychloride</ent>⟦br⟧
